      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Displays methyltransferase, positive regulation of the poly(A) polymerase and transcription elongation activities. Involved in the modification of both mRNA ends and in intermediate and late gene positive transcription elongation. At the mRNAs 5' end, methylates the ribose 2' OH group of the first transcribed nucleotide, thereby producing a 2'-O-methylpurine cap. At the 3' end, functions as a processivity factor which stimulates the activity of the viral poly(A) polymerase OPG063 that creates mRNA's poly(A) tail. In the presence of OPG102, OPG063 does not dissociate from the RNA allowing tail elongation to around 250 adenylates"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Interacts with poly(A) polymerase catalytic subunit OPG063. Interacts with OPG109 and OPG123; these interactions might help linking transcription to capping and polyadenylation"
            }
          ]
        }
